article.headline: Lehigh 72, Sacred Heart 63
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 21 points and Bryan White added 15 points and seven rebounds as Lehigh won to its second straight game, 72-63 over Sacred Heart on Sunday. Kyle Neptune added 10 points and eight rebounds for Lehigh (2-3). Luke Granato scored 16 points to lead Sacred Heart (1-3). The teams were tied at 28 at the break, and Lehigh jumped out to a quick lead in the second half with a 10-0 run. Sacred Heart rallied and cut the deficit to one on a pair of free throws by Tavio Hobson with 4:51 remaining. Baskets by Marquis Hall and White pushed Lehigh's lead back to five, and the Mountain Hawks moved out to an eight-point lead with 1:11 after a three-point play by Jason Mgebroff. Matt Szalachowski added a pair of free throws to stretch the lead to 10 points, and Lehigh closed out the win. Lehigh shot 51 percent and limited the Pioneers to 33 percent.
